cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SE 

The paper discusses a communication platform for multi-agent systems that provides trust and anonymity. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with ensuring secure communication between agents. Additionally, the platform uses AI techniques such as random-walk algorithm for anonymous communication, which makes it relevant to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The platform also involves distributed communication, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of steganography for hidden communication makes it relevant to the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the platform involves the development of middleware, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
